metadata.name: Infinite Rhythmic Universe - PROTOTYPE #84
metadata.description:
This is a prototype that generates rhythm patterns for samplers and FM synthesized sounds in web audio. Various shapes are generated reactively according to the tone according to the sound.

There are some audio post-processes available as parameters, and they are also working as visual post-processes at the same time.

using: 
* Audio for RNBO.js
* Three.js for Visuals

metadata.name: Pensado a mano #726
metadata.description:
WARNING: Read instructions so you don’t get a broken token!!
----


Q: Why haven’t you tried fx(params)?
A: Pff.. Sliders?


“Pensado a mano” explores the intersection of Generative Art and Hand Drawing. The collector, by drawing a predefined number of shapes on canvas, creates a unique hand-crafted seed that generates the final artwork. That is the only customisable param, thought by hand, which interacts with various random attributes to produce a unique composition.

“…the time we spend doing and making things, the process…”

And yet the process continues. On the background, the code generates a plottable svg.
An artificially extended process, from hand to screen, from screen to paper, that creates a new kind of mixed media.

Signed plots will soon be claimable via Artfora (tbd price + shipping)


INSTRUCTIONS

1 - Draw the requested shapes and wait to see the result. You can change the Seed Nr. slider if you don't like the selected mode.
2 - Press “C” to copy drawing to Clipboard
3 - Copy the clipboard contents to the text-input on the fx(params) sidebar

***Important. If you buy several tickets, make sure you don't mint the same Seed Nr. twice (slider)

press “S” to save the PNG, press “P” to plot the SVG


DISCLAIMER

This is a high-supply token minted during a bear market. Have Fun.

metadata.name: Streaming #116
metadata.description:
Streaming is an exploration of curl noise and rounding errors, using fx(params) to shape the piece.

My own method for producing pieces of interest is to randomise all parameters, then lock favourable aspects and experiment with altering one or two parameters. If the piece is too dark, reduce the render length or increase the stroke weight. If the piece seems too light, alter the volatility of the noise, or slow it down with increased friction. Each parameter can, of course, be explained in great detail, but in reality the best way to work with the piece is to play.

The random numbers for the piece are generated using the minter's address, meaning that what you see as a live preview will be the exact mint received.

metadata.name: All Fold: Sketch #223
metadata.description:
'All Fold: Sketch' is a generative system intended to celebrate the writing and artwork that can only be found in the pages of a sketchbook. The project itself is much like a sketch, and attempts to represent the spirit of a work-in-progress.

The fold is included as a reminder that there is always another page.

In the context of the market, the pricing of this project is intended to offer an enjoyable minting experience, while giving the opportunity to contribute to important charities.

- 60% of any primary sales will be split between "Girls Who Code" and "Cure Parkinson's"
- 60% of any royalties will be split between "Girls Who Code" and "Cure Parkinson's"

The aesthetics of this project were directly inspired by the works of Gunta Stölzl, Anni Albers, Gertrud Arndt, Kenneth Martin, and Josef Albers.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2023.

metadata.name: The Living Book #1 #48
metadata.description:
I have been exploring the medium of print for years. Mixing etching, silk-screening, offset, photocopy, risography, drawing and painting to design and craft experimental art books.From the day digital, which had always fascinated me, took over my publishing practice, I always liked to create bridges between these two worlds.

The Living Books is part of this series of hybrid and experimental works where paper and digital resonate.

This issue #1 is made of 64 pages that will be minted by collectors. A book will eventually be printed and the pages will follow the mint order. Each page exists in a cover version (c) and a xerox version (x).

Controls :

• Click to dive into each frame.
• Press C to toggle cover mode.
• Press X to toggle xerox mode.
• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Living Book #1 by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Multi-Biome #63

Inspired by Jose Margulis's "Alpine Landscape"

Designed to be viewed as if you're walking past on the gallery wall, Multi-Biome is an interative play on perspective and scale. Each landscape is created from between 50 and 200 planes, slicing the landscape along a single axis.

Click and drag to rotate.

Press "s" in live view to save a png.

metadata.name: Steps of Yu - 禹步 (Yubu) #72
metadata.description:
In Chinese mythology, Yu is known as the one who regulated the waters after the great flood, a fact he accomplished by walking through the world. The flood may be equated with primordial chaos or, in a more synchronic mode of thought, the chaos underlying the existing state of order. And the cosmic order established by Yu may be identified with the societal order instituted by the emperor in accordance with the patterns of the universe.

In this generative piece of work there are many, many chaotic and random elements at play that are brought into a state of order, resulting in intriguing and storytelling compositions similar to traditional Chinese panel-based paintings and early Japanese Manga. It is as if each panel shows a detail from a snapshot in time from the many years of effort and adventures Yu experienced battling the elements on behalf of humankind.

If you'd like to find out more about this work, visit:
http://nor44.com/steps-of-yu.html

metadata.name: The Passing of Time #290
metadata.description:
To celebrate the one-year anniversary of fx(hash), an animated piece that both signifies and illustrates the passing of time. The generative code is derived from Before/After, but adds a unique animation algorithm that causes the artwork to organically expand and contract. The art adapts to different screen sizes but will work best in full-screen mode on a wide-screen monitor.

The Passing of Time is written in plain JavaScript, with the compute-intensive t-SNE transformation implemented in AssemblyScript and compiled to WebAssembly (WASM) for maximum performance. No external libraries have been used.

<space bar>: Pause the animation.
0, 1, 2, 3, 4: Resolution, from lowest (0) to highest (4); default is 2. Try to lower the resolution if the animation isn't smooth.

50% of primary proceeds will be donated to Tezos Ukraine, https://donate.tezos.org.ua/.

Author:
Claus O. Wilke
https://clauswilke.com/art
https://twitter.com/clauswilke

metadata.name: Generative Charts #01 Sushiswap Live Data #32
metadata.description:
Live data charts pulling blockchain data in real time through The Graph decentralized network from Sushiswap subgraph (https://thegraph.com/explorer/subgraph?id=0x4bb4c1b0745ef7b4642feeccd0740dec417ca0a0-0). 

Each chart is uniquely generated. There are 14 possible options of tokens that are visualized, 6 different options of variables (i.e. price USD, liquidity USD, etc..), 7 possible ranges of dates (how many days back), 5 different line types, and a very large number of possible colors. 

Once a chart is generated, it will keep showing live data for its configuration. This does not use a centralized API endpoint, but rather triggers a micro-transaction in GRT to pay for the query to get the latest data (forever covered as part of your mint cost).

⚠️ This generative token is HIGHLY experimental ⚠️ I will buy back any token at mint price for any reason no questions asked and that will always be an option. Put it for sale at mint price and message me on twitter @esclaponr and I will buy it back.
